the respect they deserve. He will ensure our laws are updated to keep pace and stay ahead of the criminals and organized gangs, and will properly fund victim support programs.</p></div></div><div class="learning-accordian"><div class="accordion-header"><h6 class="heading-accordion">Protect Parents’ Rights and ensure school choice.</h6><div class="lynx-icon-arrow"></div></div><div class="accordion-content"><p class="paragraph-accordion">As a father of six Bill understands that it is parents who make the best choices for their children and will do all he can to protect that. Schools should nurture, educate, and protect our children by providing a safe environment in which they can flourish. Bill is determined that parents must be fully involved in the development of their children and all the decisions that affect them. Bill volunteers to teach Spanish each week to home school children. He will ensure that school choice remains at the heart of our education system in Virginia.</p></div></div><div class="taxes-accrodian"><div class="accordion-header"><h6 class="heading-accordion">Keeping personal &amp; business taxes low.</h6><div class="lynx-icon-arrow"></div></div><div class="accordion-content"><p class="paragraph-accordion">As a family man and small business owner, Bill understands the challenges we all face every day. That is why he will campaign to keep your personal taxes as low as possible so that you keep more of the money you earn, and to stop government wasting valuable public resources. He will support small businesses with a tax system that recognizes the unique challenges they face and will ensure our tax system encourages businesses to come here and create well-paid jobs in Northern Virginia, so that our local economy can thrive.</p></div></div><div class="transportation-accordian"><div class="accordion-header"><h6 class="heading-accordion">Establish a transportation system that works for Northern Virginia, and stop hard-working people from being priced off the roads.</h6><div class="lynx-icon-arrow"></div></div><div class="accordion-content"><p class="paragraph-accordion">We all understand the misery that is Northern Virginia’s road system. Despite promises from Democrats, the traffic gets worse, and the commute gets longer. Bill is determined that money is spent to tackle the problem, increase capacity, and reduce congestion. Hard working citizens are being priced off the roads by the expensive and ineffective HOV-3 which is only adding to the cost-of-living crisis for many. Stopping the war on the motorist and using smarter solutions will improve the commute without penalizing working people.</p></div></div></div></div><div class="footer _2"><div class="container-5 w-container"><div><a href="#" class="link-block-3 w-inline-block"><img src="https://assets-global.website-files.com/6425870a0fbb780e2b5b91eb/64258a22733983f6d9438a54_logo-04.svg" loading="lazy" alt="" class="image-8"/></a></div><div class="div-block-8"><ul role="list" class="nav-menu w-list-unstyled"><li class="list-item-2"><a href="/" class="nav-word footer _2 orange">Home</a><a href="/about" class="nav-word footer orange about">About</a><a href="/news" class="nav-word footer orange about">News</a><a href="/endorsements" class="nav-word footer orange about">Endorsements</a><a href="/district-30-plan" aria-current="page" class="nav-word footer orange about w--current">District 30 Plan</a><a href="/join-team-woolf" class="nav-word footer">Join Team Woolf</a><a href="#" class="nav-link-2">Donate</a></li></ul></div><div class="div-block-10"><div class="div-block-9"></div><div><div class="text-block-2">Text messaging originator opt-in data and consent will not be shared with any third parties unless required by law.<br/> <br/>Paid for by Woolf for Senate<br/> <br/>Mailing Address:<br/>Woolf for Senate<br/>P.O. Box 775<br/>Gainesville, VA 20156</div></div><div class="text-block-4">Text messaging originator opt-in data and consent will not be shared with any